  "texts": [
    "►Table 5 shows the performance of the deidentification on five document types, when each document type is excluded from or included in the training set.",
    "A Student's t-test between the \"Included\" and \"Excluded\" model for each document type did not show any statistically significant difference in F1-score performance between these pairs of models, except in the case of \"ANAPATH\" documents (F1-score p-value ¼ 0.027 < 0.05 and Fully redacted p-value ¼ 0.023 < 0.05).",
    "Abbreviations: ML, machine learning; RB, rule-based.",
    "Notes: Each result was averaged over five runs.",
    "Best results amongst \"RB,\" \"ML\" and \"Hybrid\" were highlighted in bold, and a star was added next to significantly higher results between one of \"ML\" or \"Hybrid\" methods (as determined by a Student's t-test with a p-value less than 0.05)."
  ],
